Report 0 - Out of the shadows

Through the starry void of space, a lone hunk of metal was making its way through a cloud of space rock. Whenever debris would impact its surface, the object would simply bounce off with a faint white flash illuminating the ship’s dark-brown hull at the hit location. Surrounding the craft were a dozen much smaller machines, each only big enough to hold two or three people, and shielded in a similar fashion.
At the back of the convoy was one such machine, a so-called “biped MeK” with an oversized rocket booster mounted onto its rear. Its main body was flat and roughly shaped like a tank, but it had arms and legs instead of treads, and wore a warpick-like implement in its left manipulator.

“I arrived at point 38. Commencing scan for hostiles.”

Even though the scouting report from a day ago mentioned this part of the asteroid belt to be a clear zone, young recruit Amon was clearly on edge. He reflexively gritted his teeth as he carefully double-checked the scanning results on his monitor - The board computer’s natural processing delay felt so much more painful in a real situation than in the training drills.

The lidar system marked a vast number of smaller asteroids as gray 3d-objects on the display. The aether sensor picked up 4 smaller blue points and a larger blotch at the edge of the screen, the signatures of the other MeKs and the cargo ship they were keeping watch over.

“The sector appears clear, sir. No foreign AAC signatures found. No heat sources, either. Over."

The rough voice of an old chainsmoker named Newcastle responded over the laser comms.
“Roger. Move on to point 39, mister Grand. Over.”

“Zoe, bring us to point 39. Just let me mark the location on your helmet UI… and done.”
